Online Retail Order Outcome Prediction

Executive Summary
This project presents a machine learning solution designed to predict the outcome of online retail orders, classifying them as either 'Successful' or 'At-Risk'. Leveraging a comprehensive data science approach encompassing data cleaning, exploratory data analysis, sophisticated feature engineering, and robust predictive modeling, the system aims to empower retail businesses.

The core objective is to enable proactive identification of orders likely to be cancelled, returned, or pending before fulfillment. By doing so, businesses can significantly reduce operational losses, optimize resource allocation, and enhance customer satisfaction through timely interventions for high-risk orders. The developed model demonstrates high accuracy and predictive power, offering a valuable tool for strategic decision-making in online retail operations.

