Conclusion
This project successfully delivered a highly accurate and robust machine learning system to predict online retail order outcomes. By meticulously following a structured data science pipeline, we built a model capable of distinguishing between successful and at-risk orders with exceptional performance. The LightGBM model, after hyperparameter tuning, achieved an outstanding ROC-AUC of 0.9999 on unseen data, with feature importance analysis highlighting key drivers of order success. This system enables proactive identification of high-risk orders, significantly reducing operational losses and enhancing customer satisfaction. The notebook provides a complete and reproducible workflow for integrating advanced analytics into online retail operations.
